<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-10-30T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-10-30T21:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5691: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-10-31T10:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                        1924—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 31—2:42
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>418. American consul Tientsin advises despatch of American naval vessel
                            to Tientsin to afford additional protection American life and property
                            if necessary. Ships of other nationalities now present. I have
                            recommended to commander in chief Asiatic Fleet accordingly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>